cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper focuses on developing a model predictive control strategy for demand response experiments, which falls under the domain of systems and control. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses maximum likelihood estimation to estimate the parameters of the stochastic differential equations used in the grey-box model, which is a machine learning technique. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses machine learning techniques to develop a model for demand response experiments, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper applies the developed model to demand response experiments, which is an application in the domain of computational engineering. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper describes the implementation of the model predictive control strategy, which involves software engineering techniques.
